    "Id": "chassisdef_coriolis_CRLS-486",
    "Name": "Coriolis",
    "Details": "The CRLS-486 is the FedCom Civil War era Coriolis, built around an LB-20X autocannon as its devastating centerpiece. A Targeting Computer sharpens every weapon on the frame, with a Light Gauss Rifle providing reach and a Medium Pulse Laser and ER Medium Laser adding close-range support. An Anti-Missile System offers defensive coverage. Three jump jets retain the chassis signature rear-arc ambush capability, now delivering considerably more accurate punishment on arrival.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: Accurate Weapon - AC</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.16</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limit: Right Lower</color>",
